UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 266/GA
1 (j) Any physical therapy certificate or license issued pursuant to KRS Chapter
2 327;
3 (k) Any social worker, marriage and family therapist, or professional counselor
4 certificate or license issued pursuant to KRS Chapter 335;
5 (l) A physician assistant license issued pursuant to KRS Chapter 311;[ and]
6 (m) A dietitian license or nutritionist certificate issued pursuant to KRS Chapter
7 310; and
8 (n) A speech-language pathology or audiology license issued pursuant to KRS
9 Chapter 334A;
10 (4) "Grantor" means an individual or an entity that gifts, grants, or donates moneys to
11 the Kentucky healthcare workforce investment fund established in KRS 164.0402;
12 (5) "Healthcare partner" means a grantor to the Kentucky healthcare workforce
13 investment fund that is:
14 (a) A healthcare provider as defined in KRS 367.4081;
15 (b) A healthcare facility licensed by and operating in Kentucky;
16 (c) A qualified mental health professional as defined in KRS 202A.011; or
17 (d) Any healthcare or healthcare-related association, individual, or corporation
18 doing business in and incorporated under the laws of the Commonwealth;
19 (6) "Healthcare program" means an education or training program that is a specific
20 requirement to an eligible healthcare credential, including but not limited to a high
21 school healthcare vocational program;
22 (7) "Historically underserved county" means a county of the Commonwealth with
23 enhanced workforce demands, as demonstrated by:
24 (a) Objective healthcare workforce data that demonstrates needs and demands
25 upon its healthcare workforce that exceed the statewide average; and
26 (b) Final unemployment figures calculated by the Department of Workforce
27 Development demonstrating a countywide rate of unemployment that exceeds
